Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @baby potatoes{400%grams} into 2cm chunks.

Pop the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, drain the @grilling cheese{200%grams}, then cut into slices (4 per person).

Place the cheese in a #bowl{} of cold @water{} and leave to soak.

Halve the @bell pepper{1}, discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

In a small bowl, combine the @sweet chilli sauce{2%sachets} and @mayo{2%sachets}.
Set aside.

Place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the pepper and fry, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Wipe the pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Remove the cheese slices from the water and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Rub each cheese slice with @cajun spice mix{2%sachets}, ensuring to coat both sides.

Once the pan is hot, add the cheese and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl for the salad, mix the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet}
together with @sugar{½%tsp} and @oil{2%tbsp} (double both for 4p).

Just before serving, add the @salad leaves{40%grams} to the bowl and toss to coat in
the dressing.

Pop the @tortillas{8} into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once golden, remove the cheese from the pan and cut each slice in half.

Pop the warmed tortillas onto your #plates{} and spread a spoonful of
sweet chilli mayo over each.

Top with the rocket salad, cooked peppers and golden cheese.

Serve the potatoes alongside.